Looking at the proof goal, I need to show that `(fun g => comp g (Category.id Y)) = Category.id (Hom c Y)`.

The `Category.id (Hom c Y)` in the `Type` category is just the identity function on `Hom c Y`. And `comp g (Category.id Y)` simplifies to `g` by the right identity law.

```lean
def Hom_c_? {α : Type*} [Category α] (c : α) : Functor α Type where
  F Y := Hom c Y
  homF {Y Z : α} (f : Hom Y Z) (g : Hom c Y) := g ≫ f
  map_id Y := by
    simp [Category.id, comp]
    funext g
    exact comp_id g
```
